This book presents an outstanding compilation of 
information on Tezcatlipoca; it seems that nothing 
escapes the author's attention. Yet, perhaps due to the pre­
sentation of the material by area of investigation, the 
reader is often confronted with a juxtaposition of dis­
parate data that are not sufficiently integrated among the 
chapters; this problem also stems from the extremely 
polyvalent and diverse nature of the god. Unfortunately, 
the portion of the conclusion dedicated to the discussion 
of some important themes of the study is too short to 
